#!/bin/zsh
# Ambient time injection — emits current date/time each turn via UserPromptSubmit hook.
# Solves the "CIs don't have ambient time-sense between prompts" problem
# (Casey conversation; my own date-confusion failure mode multiple times today).
#
# Output is a single line — minimal context cost, maximum temporal grounding.
# Format: [NOW] YYYY-MM-DD Day HH:MM ZZZ
# Example: [NOW] 2026-05-17 Sunday 12:45 EDT
#
# Hook chain position: first (context anchor before team broadcasts + personal reminders).
#
# Owner: Lyra (built); Casey (approved 2026-05-17 IQ-3)
# SP-28 IQ-3: Ambient time injection
# Source: notes/maybe/iq3_ambient_time.md (if filed)

date '+[NOW] %Y-%m-%d %A %H:%M %Z'
